    "body": "<p>Pricing for professional exterior cleaning in the Columbus area is project-specific, but the local market gives us a reliable planning range. This guide covers typical 2026 pricing for the services we provide most often.</p>\n\n<p><strong>Important:</strong> These are typical Greater Columbus market ranges for planning — not a quote. Your actual price depends on the size and condition of the surfaces, access, and whether multiple services are bundled.</p>\n\n<h2>Typical price ranges (single-family homes)</h2>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>House soft washing (standard 2-story):</strong> $350–$700</li>\n<li><strong>House + roof soft washing:</strong> $600–$1,200</li>\n<li><strong>Driveway / sidewalk cleaning:</strong> $150–$400</li>\n<li><strong>Deck or patio cleaning:</strong> $150–$500 (depending on size and material)</li>\n<li><strong>Full property package (house + roof + driveway + patio):</strong> $900–$2,000+</li>\n</ul>\n\n<h2>What affects the price</h2>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Size and stories</strong> — larger or multi-story homes take more time and product.</li>\n<li><strong>Condition</strong> — heavy algae, mold, or long-neglected surfaces require more work.</li>\n<li><strong>Access and obstacles</strong> — difficult access, landscaping, or tight spaces add time.</li>\n<li><strong>Surfaces included</strong> — bundling multiple surfaces usually saves money per service.</li>\n<li><strong>Roof type and pitch</strong> — steeper or more complex roofs cost more.</li>\n</ul>\n\n<h2>Soft washing vs pressure washing pricing</h2>\n<p>Soft washing (house, roof, deck) is generally priced per surface or package. Driveway and hardscape pressure washing is often priced by the square foot or as an add-on. A good quote will clearly separate the services and explain what method will be used on each surface.</p>\n\n<h2>How to get the best value</h2>\n<p>Focus on the company’s process, chemicals, insurance, and experience rather than the lowest price. A slightly higher price for proper soft washing and good prep almost always beats a cheap pressure-wash job that damages surfaces or fails to remove growth at the root.</p>\n\n<p>Get a free, written estimate that spells out exactly what will be done on each surface. That’s the best way to compare apples to apples.</p>"
